Footer: For a Pet Food Website
This project is part of my Web Development Daily Practice Challenge, where I create a new mini-project every day.

📜 Project Overview
The Footer for a Pet Food Website is a reusable component designed to enhance user engagement and website navigation. It features a modern design with structured sections for product categories, newsletter subscription, and social media links.

✨ Features:
Newsletter Subscription: Users can sign up to receive updates.
Product Navigation: Clear and structured product categories for ease of use.
Social Media Integration: Links with icons to popular platforms (Bootstrap framework).

Modern Styling:
Used Google Fonts for typography.
Applied CSS properties for proper alignment, spacing, and color coordination.
Clean and responsive design.

🔧 Technologies Used:
HTML: Structured with divs, span tags, anchor tags, and buttons.
CSS: Styled for font size, weight, and color, along with responsive spacing.
Bootstrap Framework: Used for adding icons and simplifying UI elements.

🛠️ How to Use:
Clone or download the repository.
Open index.html in your browser to view the footer.
Customize the content and styling to match your project requirements.

🎯 Why This Project?
This footer design demonstrates the ability to create a functional and visually appealing component for websites. It is reusable and adaptable, making it suitable for various projects, especially those in e-commerce.

⭐ Star the repository if you find it helpful, and feel free to share your feedback! 😊
